//middlewares
app.use(express.static('public'));
//at the place of 'public' incase if we placed any other name then it not printed 
//By default express does not allow to serve with static files so we need to enable it by using=> app.use(express.static('public'));


res.sendFile() and res.render() both are different
//The render method works when you have a templating engine, such as Handlebars or Jade, in use.
//The sendfile method, on the other hand, simply sends a given file to the client, regardless of the type and contents of the file


app.set('view engine', 'ejs');
//the above one is required for render file(like if file will be saving index.ejs)
.
